  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/398",
  "title": "RefinementList not updating its underlying item DOM",
  "body": "After refining on one of the items of the RefinementList, the CSS rule I put in place to highlight the refined item was not applied. Funny thing is as soon as I move the cursor hover the item, my CSS rules applies.\n\n![bug](http://g.recordit.co/P5xzmc7O58.gif)\n\nWe're currently rendering the items of a RefinementList using:\n\n``` jsx\n      <div\n        className={cssClassItem}\n        key={facetValue[this.props.facetNameKey]}\n        onClick={this.handleClick.bind(this, facetValue[this.props.facetNameKey])}\n      >\n        <Template data={templateData} templateKey=\"item\" {...this.props.templateProps} />\n        {subList}\n      </div>\n```\n\nChanging the `key` to `facetValue[this.props.facetNameKey] + '/' + facetValue.isRefined + '/' + facetValue.count` fixes the issue.\n",
